<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="scroll-smooth">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Infographic: Architecting Modern Document Intelligence</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- Chosen Palette: Energetic & Playful -->
    <!-- Narrative & Structure Plan: The infographic tells a story in four acts. Act 1: "The Evolution," introduces the core problem and the shift from OCR to IDP. Act 2: "The Cloud Titans," provides a head-to-head comparison of the major managed platforms (Azure, Google, AWS) using bar charts and feature callouts. Act 3: "The New Challengers," contrasts the established cloud platforms with the disruptive approaches of Direct LLM APIs and Self-Hosted models, using donut charts and flow diagrams. Act 4: "The Strategic Playbook," concludes with a clear, use-case-driven recommendation guide, helping the user choose the right path. This narrative structure guides the user from foundational knowledge to actionable strategy. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
        - Data Point: Minimum training documents for custom models (Azure, Google). Goal: Compare. Viz: Bar Chart. Justification: A bar chart provides a direct, simple visual comparison of the low data requirements, highlighting Google's zero-shot advantage. Library: Chart.js (Canvas).
        - Data Point: Pricing comparison of cloud platforms. Goal: Compare. Viz: Grouped Bar Chart. Justification: Effectively compares multiple cost dimensions (e.g., pre-built vs. custom) across the three main competitors in a single view. Library: Chart.js (Canvas).
        - Data Point: Self-Hosted Pipeline. Goal: Organize/Inform. Viz: HTML/CSS Flow Diagram. Justification: A styled flexbox layout clearly illustrates the sequence of components in a self-hosted solution without using forbidden SVG/Mermaid. Method: HTML/CSS with Tailwind.
        - Data Point: Strategic Decision Criteria (Effort vs. Control). Goal: Compare/Relationships. Viz: Bubble Chart. Justification: A bubble chart can visually represent three dimensions (e.g., X-axis: Effort, Y-axis: Control, Bubble Size: Cost), making complex trade-offs intuitive. Library: Chart.js (Canvas).
        - Data Point: Market Share/Preference (Conceptual). Goal: Inform. Viz: Donut Chart. Justification: A donut chart is a visually engaging way to show the composition of different approaches in the market. Library: Chart.js (Canvas).
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            background-color: #0D1B2A; /* Deep Navy Blue from Palette */
        }
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            height: 350px;
            max-height: 400px;
        }
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .chart-container {
                height: 400px;
            }
        }
        .stat-card {
            background-color: #1B263B; /* Darker Shade */
            border: 1px solid #415A77; /* Mid Blue */
        }
        .text-accent {
            color: #FFD166; /* Vibrant Yellow */
        }
        .text-highlight {
            color: #EF476F; /* Vibrant Pink */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="text-white">

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

        <!-- Header -->
        <header class="text-center mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold mb-4">
                The <span class="text-accent">Document Intelligence</span> Playbook
            </h1>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                From Scanned Pages to Structured JSON: A Visual Guide to Modern Data Extraction.
            </p>
        </header>

        <!-- Section 1: The Evolution -->
        <section class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-10">
                The Leap from <span class="text-gray-400">OCR</span> to <span class="text-highlight">Intelligent Automation</span>
            </h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
                <div class="stat-card p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Then: OCR</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Optical Character Recognition was a revolution in digitizing text. It converts images to raw text strings, but that's where it stops.</p>
                    <div class="bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-md font-mono text-sm text-gray-400">
                        "123 Main St. Total: $599.99 INV-12345"
                    </div>
                     <p class="text-sm mt-3 text-gray-400">It sees text, but understands nothing. Developers are left to write brittle, layout-specific rules to find the data they need.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-highlight">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-highlight">Now: IDP</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Intelligent Document Processing uses AI to understand context, classifying documents and extracting data into structured JSON, ready for any application.</p>
                    <div class="bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-md font-mono text-sm text-green-400">
                        <pre>{
  "address": "123 Main St.",
  "invoice_id": "INV-12345",
  "total": 599.99
}</pre>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-sm mt-3 text-gray-400">It delivers pre-interpreted, structured data, automating entire workflows.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2: The Cloud Titans -->
        <section class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-10">The Cloud Titans: Managed IDP Platforms</h2>
            <p class="text-center text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">Azure, Google Cloud, and AWS offer powerful, managed "buy" solutions. Here's how they stack up on key features.</p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
                <div class="stat-card p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Minimum Docs for Custom Training</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 text-center mb-4">Lower is better. Google's GenAI approach allows for "zero-shot" extraction, a major advantage for rapid deployment.</p>
                    <div class="chart-container h-64 md:h-80">
                        <canvas id="trainingDataChart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">The Customization Playbook</h3>
                    <ul class="space-y-4">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-accent font-bold text-2xl mr-4">A</span>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">Azure: The Dual-Model Approach</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Offers both fast 'Template' models for fixed layouts and flexible 'Neural' models for variable ones.</p>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-highlight font-bold text-2xl mr-4">G</span>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">Google: The GenAI Powerhouse</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Leverages foundation models for zero-shot extraction, requiring no initial training data.</p>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                         <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-blue-400 font-bold text-2xl mr-4">W</span>
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">AWS: The Query Master</h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Customizes by training 'Adapters' to answer specific, natural language questions about your documents.</p>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Section 3: The New Challengers -->
        <section class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-10">The New Challengers</h2>
            <p class="text-center text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">Two powerful alternatives are reshaping the landscape: using general-purpose LLMs directly, or building your own solution with open-source tools.</p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="stat-card p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Direct LLM APIs: The Ultimate Flex</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 text-center mb-4">Leverage models like GPT-4o or Gemini to "read" any document. Unmatched flexibility, but watch for higher latency and potential "hallucinations".</p>
                    <div class="chart-container h-80">
                        <canvas id="llmDonutChart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card p-6 rounded-lg">
                     <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Self-Hosted: Maximum Control</h3>
                     <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 text-center mb-6">Build your own pipeline for total data privacy and the lowest long-term cost at extreme scale. Requires significant ML expertise.</p>
                     <div class="space-y-2">
                        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-2">
                             <div class="bg-gray-700 p-3 rounded-md text-center"><p class="font-semibold text-sm">Document Input</p></div>
                             <div class="text-2xl text-accent">&rarr;</div>
                             <div class="bg-gray-700 p-3 rounded-md text-center"><p class="font-semibold text-sm">Open-Source OCR</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">(Tesseract)</p></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex justify-center"><div class="text-2xl text-accent">&darr;</div></div>
                        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-2">
                             <div class="bg-gray-700 p-3 rounded-md text-center"><p class="font-semibold text-sm">Structured JSON</p></div>
                             <div class="text-2xl text-accent">&larr;</div>
                             <div class="bg-gray-700 p-3 rounded-md text-center"><p class="font-semibold text-sm">LayoutLM Model</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">(Fine-Tuned)</p></div>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 4: The Strategic Playbook -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-10">The Strategic Playbook: Choosing Your Path</h2>
            <p class="text-center text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">The right choice depends on your documents, volume, and in-house expertise. This framework guides your decision.</p>
            
            <div class="stat-card p-6 md:p-8 rounded-lg mb-12">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-center mb-4">The Decision Matrix: Effort vs. Control vs. Cost</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 text-center mb-6">This chart visualizes the fundamental trade-offs. Bubble size represents relative long-term cost at scale.</p>
                <div class="chart-container h-96">
                    <canvas id="decisionBubbleChart"></canvas>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="bg-white text-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-highlight">Scenario A: Standard Forms (W-2s)</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm">You have high volumes of fixed-layout documents. Reliability and speed are key.</p>
                    <p class="font-semibold mt-3">Recommendation: <span class="text-blue-600">Managed IDP with a Pre-Built Model.</span></p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white text-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-highlight">Scenario B: Variable Invoices</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm">You process invoices from thousands of vendors with unpredictable layouts.</p>
                    <p class="font-semibold mt-3">Recommendation: <span class="text-blue-600">Hybrid Approach (IDP + LLM Fallback).</span></p>
                </div>
                 <div class="bg-white text-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-highlight">Scenario C: Unstructured Contracts</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm">You need to extract semantic meaning, not just key-value pairs.</p>
                    <p class="font-semibold mt-3">Recommendation: <span class="text-blue-600">Direct Multimodal LLM API.</span></p>
                </div>
                 <div class="bg-white text-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-highlight">Scenario D: Max Data Privacy</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm">Data cannot leave your environment. You have a skilled MLOps team.</p>
                    <p class="font-semibold mt-3">Recommendation: <span class="text-blue-600">Self-Hosted Open-Source Pipeline.</span></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>

<script>
const FONT_COLOR = '#E0E1DD'; // Off-white for text
const GRID_COLOR = 'rgba(65, 90, 119, 0.5)'; // Mid Blue with transparency
const PALETTE = {
    pink: '#EF476F',
    yellow: '#FFD166',
    green: '#06D6A0',
    blue: '#118AB2',
    navy: '#073B4C',
};

const tooltipPlugin = {
    plugins: {
        legend: {
            labels: {
                color: FONT_COLOR,
                font: {
                    size: 14
                }
            }
        },
        tooltip: {
            callbacks: {
                title: function(tooltipItems) {
                    const item = tooltipItems[0];
                    let label = item.chart.data.labels[item.dataIndex];
                    if (Array.isArray(label)) {
                      return label.join(' ');
                    } else {
                      return label;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
};

function wrapLabel(str, maxWidth) {
    if (str.length <= maxWidth) return str;
    const words = str.split(' ');
    const lines = [];
    let currentLine = '';
    for (const word of words) {
        if ((currentLine + word).length > maxWidth) {
            lines.push(currentLine.trim());
            currentLine = '';
        }
        currentLine += word + ' ';
    }
    lines.push(currentLine.trim());
    return lines.filter(line => line.length > 0);
}

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    // Chart 1: Training Data
    const trainingDataCtx = document.getElementById('trainingDataChart').getContext('2d');
    new Chart(trainingDataCtx, {
        type: 'bar',
        data: {
            labels: ['Azure (Custom Models)', 'Google (GenAI Extractor)'],
            datasets: [{
                label: 'Minimum Documents Required',
                data: [5, 0],
                backgroundColor: [PALETTE.blue, PALETTE.green],
                borderColor: [PALETTE.blue, PALETTE.green],
                borderWidth: 1,
                barThickness: 40
            }]
        },
        options: {
            ...tooltipPlugin,
            responsive: true,
            maintainAspectRatio: false,
            indexAxis: 'y',
            scales: {
                x: {
                    beginAtZero: true,
                    ticks: { color: FONT_COLOR, stepSize: 1 },
                    grid: { color: GRID_COLOR }
                },
                y: {
                    ticks: { color: FONT_COLOR, font: { size: 14 } },
                    grid: { display: false }
                }
            }
        }
    });

    // Chart 2: LLM Donut
    const llmDonutCtx = document.getElementById('llmDonutChart').getContext('2d');
    new Chart(llmDonutCtx, {
        type: 'doughnut',
        data: {
            labels: ['Flexibility', 'Speed of Development', 'Potential Latency', 'Risk of Hallucination'],
            datasets: [{
                data: [40, 30, 15, 15],
                backgroundColor: [PALETTE.green, PALETTE.yellow, PALETTE.pink, '#D90429'],
                borderColor: '#1B263B',
                borderWidth: 4
            }]
        },
        options: {
            ...tooltipPlugin,
            responsive: true,
            maintainAspectRatio: false,
            cutout: '60%',
            plugins: {
                ...tooltipPlugin.plugins,
                title: {
                    display: true,
                    text: 'LLM API Trade-Offs',
                    color: FONT_COLOR,
                    font: { size: 16 }
                }
            }
        }
    });
    
    // Chart 3: Decision Bubble Chart
    const decisionBubbleCtx = document.getElementById('decisionBubbleChart').getContext('2d');
    new Chart(decisionBubbleCtx, {
        type: 'bubble',
        data: {
            datasets: [{
                label: 'Managed IDP',
                data: [{ x: 3, y: 7, r: 15 }],
                backgroundColor: PALETTE.blue,
            }, {
                label: 'Direct LLM API',
                data: [{ x: 2, y: 9, r: 12 }],
                backgroundColor: PALETTE.green,
            }, {
                label: 'Self-Hosted OS',
                data: [{ x: 9, y: 10, r: 10 }],
                backgroundColor: PALETTE.pink,
            }]
        },
        options: {
            ...tooltipPlugin,
            responsive: true,
            maintainAspectRatio: false,
            scales: {
                x: {
                    min: 0,
                    max: 10,
                    title: { display: true, text: 'Initial Development Effort', color: FONT_COLOR },
                    ticks: { color: FONT_COLOR },
                    grid: { color: GRID_COLOR }
                },
                y: {
                    min: 0,
                    max: 10,
                    title: { display: true, text: 'Flexibility & Control', color: FONT_COLOR },
                    ticks: { color: FONT_COLOR },
                    grid: { color: GRID_COLOR }
                }
            },
            plugins: {
                ...tooltipPlugin.plugins,
                tooltip: {
                    callbacks: {
                        label: function(context) {
                            return `${context.dataset.label}: (Effort: ${context.parsed.x}, Control: ${context.parsed.y}, Cost: ${context.raw.r})`;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    });

});
</script>
</body>
</html>
